---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';
import WireframeBackground from '../../components/WireframeBackground.astro';
---

<Layout title="Intelligent Document Retrieval Software: Features to Look For in 2025">
  <main>
    <!-- Hero Section -->
    <section class="relative min-h-[60vh] flex items-center justify-center wireframe-bg overflow-hidden">
      <WireframeBackground />
      <div class="relative z-10 max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 py-32 text-center">
        <div class="animate-slide-up">
          <p class="text-primary font-orbitron text-sm tracking-wider mb-4 matrix-text-shadow">
            NEXT-GENERATION TECHNOLOGY
          </p>
          <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-6xl font-orbitron font-bold mb-6 text-white">
            Intelligent Document Retrieval Software: <span class="text-primary">Features to Look For</span> in 2025
          </h1>
          <p class="text-xl md:text-2xl text-gray-300 max-w-4xl mx-auto mb-12 leading-relaxed">
            Essential capabilities and advanced features that define cutting-edge document retrieval systems in the modern enterprise landscape.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Article Content -->
    <article class="py-16 bg-black">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6">
        
        <!-- Hero Image -->
        <div class="mb-12">
          <img 
            src="https://images.pexels.com/photos/3184405/pexels-photo-3184405.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&h=400&w=800" 
            alt="Intelligent document retrieval software interface with advanced search capabilities" 
            class="w-full h-64 object-cover rounded-xl border border-primary/20"
          />
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400 mt-2 text-center">Modern intelligent document retrieval interface showcasing advanced search capabilities</p>
        </div>

        <!-- Introduction -->
        <div class="glass-morphism p-8 rounded-xl mb-12">
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-200 leading-relaxed mb-6">
            The document retrieval software landscape has evolved dramatically in 2025, with artificial intelligence fundamentally transforming how organizations find, access, and utilize their information assets. Modern intelligent document retrieval systems go far beyond simple keyword matching, offering <strong class="text-primary">contextual understanding, predictive recommendations, and automated insights</strong> that were impossible with previous generations of technology.
          </p>
          
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-200 leading-relaxed">
            Organizations investing in next-generation document retrieval software report <strong class="text-primary">40-60% improvements in knowledge worker productivity</strong> and <strong class="text-primary">80% reduction in time-to-insight</strong> for critical business decisions, according to Forrester's 2025 Enterprise Content Management report.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- What is Intelligent Document Retrieval Software -->
        <section class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-orbitron font-bold text-primary mb-6">What is intelligent document retrieval software?</h2>
          
          <div class="glass-morphism p-8 rounded-xl mb-8">
            <p class="text-gray-200 leading-relaxed mb-6">
              Intelligent document retrieval software represents the convergence of artificial intelligence, natural language processing, and advanced search technologies to create systems that understand document content, user intent, and organizational context. These platforms go beyond traditional search by providing semantic understanding, automated summarization, and intelligent recommendations.
            </p>
            
            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
              <div>
                <h3 class="text-xl font-orbitron font-bold text-white mb-4">Core Intelligence Capabilities</h3>
                <ul class="text-gray-200 space-y-3">
                  <li class="flex items-start">
                    <span class="text-primary mr-2">•</span>
                    <span><strong class="text-primary">Semantic Search:</strong> Understands meaning and context, not just keywords</span>
                  </li>
                  <li class="flex items-start">
                    <span class="text-primary mr-2">•</span>
                    <span><strong class="text-primary">Content Summarization:</strong> Automatically generates document summaries and key insights</span>
                  </li>
                  <li class="flex items-start">
                    <span class="text-primary mr-2">•</span>
                    <span><strong class="text-primary">Predictive Suggestions:</strong> Recommends relevant documents before users search</span>
                  </li>
                  <li class="flex items-start">
                    <span class="text-primary mr-2">•</span>
                    <span><strong class="text-primary">Auto-Classification:</strong> Organizes documents by content, not manual tags</span>
                  </li>
                </ul>
              </div>
              
              <div>
                <h3 class="text-xl font-orbitron font-bold text-white mb-4">Advanced Features (2025)</h3>
                <ul class="text-gray-200 space-y-3">
                  <li class="flex items-start">
                    <span class="text-primary mr-2">•</span>
                    <span><strong class="text-primary">Multi-Modal Understanding:</strong> Processes text, images, charts, and diagrams</span>
                  </li>
                  <li class="flex items-start">
                    <span class="text-primary mr-2">•</span>
                    <span><strong class="text-primary">Conversational Queries:</strong> Natural language interaction with document repositories</span>
                  </li>
                  <li class="flex items-start">
                    <span class="text-primary mr-2">•</span>
                    <span><strong class="text-primary">Real-Time Learning:</strong> Adapts to user behavior and organizational patterns</span>
                  </li>
                  <li class="flex items-start">
                    <span class="text-primary mr-2">•</span>
                    <span><strong class="text-primary">Cross-Repository Search:</strong> Unified search across multiple systems</span>
                  </li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Technology Evolution -->
          <div class="bg-primary/80 border border-primary/20 p-6 rounded-xl">
            <h3 class="font-orbitron font-bold text-primary mb-3">Evolution from Traditional to Intelligent Systems</h3>
            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 text-center">
              <div class="bg-black/90 p-4 rounded-lg">
                <h4 class="font-orbitron font-bold text-white mb-2">2020-2022</h4>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-300">Keyword-based search with basic filters</p>
              </div>
              <div class="bg-black/90 p-4 rounded-lg">
                <h4 class="font-orbitron font-bold text-white mb-2">2023-2024</h4>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-300">AI-enhanced search with semantic understanding</p>
              </div>
              <div class="bg-primary/80 p-4 rounded-lg">
                <h4 class="font-orbitron font-bold text-primary mb-2">2025+</h4>
                <p class="text-sm text-white">Fully intelligent, conversational document intelligence</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Key Benefits -->
        <section class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-orbitron font-bold text-primary mb-6">Key Benefits of intelligent document retrieval software</h2>
          
          <div class="space-y-8">
            <!-- Productivity & Efficiency -->
            <div class="glass-morphism p-8 rounded-xl">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-orbitron font-bold text-white mb-4">Dramatic Productivity Improvements</h3>
              <p class="text-gray-200 leading-relaxed mb-6">
                Modern intelligent document retrieval software eliminates the frustrating cycle of searching, reviewing, and re-searching that characterizes traditional document management. Organizations report that knowledge workers regain an average of <strong class="text-primary">2.5 hours per day</strong> previously lost to document hunting and manual information synthesis.
              </p>
              
              <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
                <div class="bg-black/90 p-4 rounded-lg">
                  <h4 class="font-bold text-primary mb-2">Before Intelligent Retrieval</h4>
                  <ul class="text-gray-300 text-sm space-y-1">
                    <li>• 30+ minutes per complex search</li>
                    <li>• Multiple system logins required</li>
                    <li>• Manual review of 10-20 documents</li>
                    <li>• 40-60% relevant results</li>
                    <li>• No cross-reference capabilities</li>
                  </ul>
                </div>
                <div class="bg-primary/80 p-4 rounded-lg">
                  <h4 class="font-bold text-primary mb-2">With Intelligent Systems</h4>
                  <ul class="text-gray-300 text-sm space-y-1">
                    <li>• 2-3 minutes for comprehensive answers</li>
                    <li>• Single interface across all repositories</li>
                    <li>• Automatic synthesis and summarization</li>
                    <li>• 85-95% relevance rate</li>
                    <li>• Automatic relationship discovery</li>
                  </ul>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Decision-Making Enhancement -->
            <div class="glass-morphism p-8 rounded-xl">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-orbitron font-bold text-white mb-4">Enhanced Decision-Making Capabilities</h3>
              <p class="text-gray-200 leading-relaxed mb-4">
                Intelligent retrieval systems don't just find documents—they provide analytical insights, identify patterns across multiple sources, and highlight potential conflicts or gaps in information. This capability is particularly valuable for strategic planning, risk assessment, and compliance monitoring.
              </p>
              
              <div class="bg-primary/80 border border-primary/20 p-4 rounded-lg">
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 italic mb-3">
                  "Our strategic planning process improved dramatically when we implemented intelligent document retrieval. The system automatically identifies conflicting data points across different reports and highlights areas needing executive attention."
                </p>
                <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">- VP Strategy, Fortune 500 Manufacturing Company</p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Compliance & Risk Management -->
            <div class="glass-morphism p-8 rounded-xl">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-orbitron font-bold text-white mb-4">Automated Compliance & Risk Monitoring</h3>
              <p class="text-gray-200 leading-relaxed mb-4">
                Intelligent systems continuously monitor document repositories for compliance violations, outdated policies, and regulatory changes. This proactive approach reduces compliance risk by up to <strong class="text-primary">90%</strong> and ensures organizations stay current with evolving regulations.
              </p>
              
              <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 text-center">
                <div class="bg-black/90 p-4 rounded-lg">
                  <div class="text-2xl font-orbitron font-bold text-primary">90%</div>
                  <div class="text-sm text-gray-300">Reduction in compliance violations</div>
                </div>
                <div class="bg-black/90 p-4 rounded-lg">
                  <div class="text-2xl font-orbitron font-bold text-primary">24/7</div>
                  <div class="text-sm text-gray-300">Continuous monitoring</div>
                </div>
                <div class="bg-black/90 p-4 rounded-lg">
                  <div class="text-2xl font-orbitron font-bold text-primary">99.7%</div>
                  <div class="text-sm text-gray-300">Accuracy in policy updates</div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Essential Features -->
        <section class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-orbitron font-bold text-primary mb-6">Essential Features for 2025</h2>
          
          <div class="glass-morphism p-8 rounded-xl mb-8">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-orbitron font-bold text-white mb-6">Must-Have Intelligent Capabilities</h3>
            
            <div class="space-y-8">
              <!-- Natural Language Processing -->
              <div class="border border-primary/20 p-6 rounded-lg">
                <h4 class="font-bold text-primary mb-3">Advanced Natural Language Processing</h4>
                <p class="text-gray-200 mb-4">
                  Modern systems must understand context, intent, and nuance in user queries. Look for platforms that support conversational search, follow-up questions, and disambiguation of ambiguous terms. The best systems maintain conversation context across multiple queries.
                </p>
                <div class="bg-black/90 p-3 rounded">
                  <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><strong class="text-primary">Example:</strong> "Show me the latest marketing budget discussions from Q4 board meetings" should understand that you want financial documents from board meeting minutes, not general marketing materials.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
              
              <!-- Multi-Modal Understanding -->
              <div class="border border-primary/20 p-6 rounded-lg">
                <h4 class="font-bold text-primary mb-3">Multi-Modal Content Processing</h4>
                <p class="text-gray-200 mb-4">
                  2025's leading systems process not just text, but images, charts, diagrams, videos, and audio content. This comprehensive understanding enables retrieval based on visual elements, data trends in charts, or specific information mentioned in recorded meetings.
                </p>
                <ul class="text-gray-300 text-sm space-y-1 ml-4">
                  <li>• OCR with 99.5%+ accuracy for scanned documents</li>
                  <li>• Chart and graph data extraction</li>
                  <li>• Video content transcription and indexing</li>
                  <li>• Image recognition and categorization</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
              
              <!-- Real-Time Learning -->
              <div class="border border-primary/20 p-6 rounded-lg">
                <h4 class="font-bold text-primary mb-3">Adaptive Learning & Personalization</h4>
                <p class="text-gray-200 mb-4">
                  Intelligent systems learn from user behavior, search patterns, and feedback to provide increasingly personalized results. The software should adapt to individual user preferences, departmental workflows, and organizational terminology over time.
                </p>
                <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
                  <div class="bg-primary/80 p-3 rounded">
                    <div class="font-bold text-primary text-sm">Individual Learning</div>
                    <div class="text-xs text-gray-300">Personal search history and preferences</div>
                  </div>
                  <div class="bg-primary/80 p-3 rounded">
                    <div class="font-bold text-primary text-sm">Organizational Learning</div>
                    <div class="text-xs text-gray-300">Company-wide patterns and terminology</div>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Advanced Features -->
        <section class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-orbitron font-bold text-primary mb-6">Advanced Features Comparison</h2>
          
          <div class="overflow-x-auto mb-8">
            <table class="w-full bg-black/90 border border-primary/20 rounded-xl overflow-hidden">
              <thead class="bg-primary/80">
                <tr>
                  <th class="text-left p-4 font-orbitron font-bold text-white">Feature Category</th>
                  <th class="text-left p-4 font-orbitron font-bold text-white">Basic Systems</th>
                  <th class="text-left p-4 font-orbitron font-bold text-white">Intelligent Systems (2025)</th>
                </tr>
              </thead>
              <tbody>
                <tr class="border-t border-primary/10">
                  <td class="p-4 text-primary font-bold">Search Capability</td>
                  <td class="p-4 text-gray-200">Keyword matching</td>
                  <td class="p-4 text-gray-200">Semantic understanding + intent recognition</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="border-t border-primary/10">
                  <td class="p-4 text-primary font-bold">Result Presentation</td>
                  <td class="p-4 text-gray-200">Document links list</td>
                  <td class="p-4 text-gray-200">Synthesized answers + source citations</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="border-t border-primary/10">
                  <td class="p-4 text-primary font-bold">Learning Capability</td>
                  <td class="p-4 text-gray-200">Static algorithms</td>
                  <td class="p-4 text-gray-200">Continuous adaptation to user patterns</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="border-t border-primary/10">
                  <td class="p-4 text-primary font-bold">Content Understanding</td>
                  <td class="p-4 text-gray-200">Text only</td>
                  <td class="p-4 text-gray-200">Multi-modal (text, images, charts, audio)</td>
                </tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>
          </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Use Cases and Examples -->
        <section class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-orbitron font-bold text-primary mb-6">Use Cases and Examples</h2>
          
          <div class="space-y-8">
            <!-- Research & Development -->
            <div class="glass-morphism p-8 rounded-xl">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-orbitron font-bold text-white mb-4">Research & Development Organizations</h3>
              <p class="text-gray-200 leading-relaxed mb-4">
                R&D teams managing thousands of research papers, technical specifications, and experimental data benefit enormously from intelligent retrieval. The system can identify research trends, find related studies across different time periods, and suggest novel connections between seemingly unrelated work.
              </p>
              
              <div class="bg-primary/80 border border-primary/20 p-4 rounded-lg">
                <h4 class="font-bold text-primary mb-2">Case Study: Pharmaceutical Research Company</h4>
                <p class="text-gray-300 text-sm mb-3">
                  A leading pharmaceutical company implemented intelligent document retrieval across 2.3 million research documents, clinical trial data, and regulatory submissions spanning 15 years.
                </p>
                <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 text-center">
                  <div class="bg-black/90 p-3 rounded">
                    <div class="text-lg font-orbitron font-bold text-primary">78%</div>
                    <div class="text-xs text-gray-300">Faster literature reviews</div>
                  </div>
                  <div class="bg-black/90 p-3 rounded">
                    <div class="text-lg font-orbitron font-bold text-primary">23%</div>
                    <div class="text-xs text-gray-300">Increase in novel research connections</div>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Financial Services -->
            <div class="glass-morphism p-8 rounded-xl">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-orbitron font-bold text-white mb-4">Financial Services & Risk Analysis</h3>
              <p class="text-gray-200 leading-relaxed mb-4">
                Financial institutions use intelligent retrieval to analyze market research, regulatory documents, risk assessments, and client portfolios. The system can identify risk patterns across multiple clients, track regulatory changes, and provide real-time insights for investment decisions.
              </p>
              
              <div class="bg-black/90 p-4 rounded-lg">
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 italic">
                  "Our risk assessment process went from 3 days to 3 hours. The system automatically pulls relevant market data, regulatory updates, and historical precedents to provide comprehensive risk profiles." - Risk Management Director, Investment Bank
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Legal & Compliance -->
            <div class="glass-morphism p-8 rounded-xl">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-orbitron font-bold text-white mb-4">Legal Research & Compliance Monitoring</h3>
              <p class="text-gray-200 leading-relaxed mb-4">
                Law firms and corporate legal departments leverage intelligent retrieval for case research, contract analysis, and regulatory compliance. The system can identify relevant precedents, analyze contract clauses for risk, and monitor regulatory changes across multiple jurisdictions.
              </p>
              
              <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
                <div class="bg-primary/80 p-4 rounded-lg text-center">
                  <div class="text-xl font-orbitron font-bold text-primary">85%</div>
                  <div class="text-sm text-gray-300">Faster legal research</div>
                </div>
                <div class="bg-primary/80 p-4 rounded-lg text-center">
                  <div class="text-xl font-orbitron font-bold text-primary">97%</div>
                  <div class="text-sm text-gray-300">Compliance accuracy rate</div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Best Practices and Tools -->
        <section class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-orbitron font-bold text-primary mb-6">Best Practices and Tools</h2>
          
          <div class="glass-morphism p-8 rounded-xl mb-8">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-orbitron font-bold text-white mb-6">Selection Criteria for 2025</h3>
            
            <div class="space-y-6">
              <div class="border border-primary/20 p-6 rounded-lg">
                <h4 class="font-bold text-primary mb-3">1. Evaluate AI Model Capabilities</h4>
                <p class="text-gray-200 mb-3">
                  Assess the underlying AI models for accuracy, language support, and domain-specific understanding. Leading platforms use ensemble approaches combining multiple specialized models rather than relying on single, general-purpose AI systems.
                </p>
                <div class="bg-black/90 p-3 rounded text-sm text-gray-300">
                  <strong>Key Metrics:</strong> Semantic similarity accuracy >95%, query response time &lt;3 seconds, multi-language support
                </div>
              </div>
              
              <div class="border border-primary/20 p-6 rounded-lg">
                <h4 class="font-bold text-primary mb-3">2. Integration & Scalability Assessment</h4>
                <p class="text-gray-200 mb-3">
                  Ensure the platform integrates seamlessly with your existing document repositories, security frameworks, and workflow systems. Scalability testing should include both document volume and concurrent user capacity.
                </p>
                <ul class="text-gray-300 text-sm space-y-1 ml-4">
                  <li>• Native integration with Microsoft 365, Google Workspace, Box</li>
                  <li>• API-first architecture for custom integrations</li>
                  <li>• Support for 10M+ documents without performance degradation</li>
                  <li>• Horizontal scaling capabilities for growing organizations</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
              
              <div class="border border-primary/20 p-6 rounded-lg">
                <h4 class="font-bold text-primary mb-3">3. Security & Governance Framework</h4>
                <p class="text-gray-200">
                  Verify that the platform maintains your organization's security posture while enabling intelligent retrieval. Look for granular access controls, audit logging, data residency options, and compliance certifications relevant to your industry.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Leading Platforms -->
          <div class="bg-black/90 border border-primary/20 p-6 rounded-xl">
            <h3 class="font-orbitron font-bold text-primary mb-4">Leading Intelligent Retrieval Platforms (2025)</h3>
            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
              <div class="space-y-4">
                <div class="bg-primary/80 p-4 rounded-lg">
                  <h4 class="font-bold text-white mb-2">Enterprise-Grade Solutions</h4>
                  <ul class="text-gray-300 text-sm space-y-1">
                    <li>• Microsoft Copilot for Microsoft 365</li>
                    <li>• Google Cloud Document AI</li>
                    <li>• Amazon Kendra with Bedrock</li>
                    <li>• IBM Watson Discovery</li>
                  </ul>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="space-y-4">
                <div class="bg-primary/80 p-4 rounded-lg">
                  <h4 class="font-bold text-white mb-2">Specialized Solutions</h4>
                  <ul class="text-gray-300 text-sm space-y-1">
                    <li>• Notion AI for knowledge management</li>
                    <li>• Glean for enterprise search</li>
                    <li>• Algolia AI Search</li>
                    <li>• Custom RAG implementations</li>
                  </ul>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <!-- FAQs -->
        <section class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-orbitron font-bold text-primary mb-6">FAQs</h2>
          
          <div class="space-y-6">
            <div class="glass-morphism p-6 rounded-xl">
              <h3 class="font-bold text-white mb-3">How does intelligent document retrieval handle different file formats?</h3>
              <p class="text-gray-200 leading-relaxed">
                Modern systems process 50+ file formats including PDFs, Word documents, Excel spreadsheets, PowerPoint presentations, images, videos, and even legacy formats. Advanced OCR technology handles scanned documents with 99.5%+ accuracy, while specialized parsers extract structured data from complex formats like CAD files and scientific datasets.
              </p>
            </div>
            
            <div class="glass-morphism p-6 rounded-xl">
              <h3 class="font-bold text-white mb-3">What's the typical ROI timeline for intelligent document retrieval software?</h3>
              <p class="text-gray-200 leading-relaxed">
                Organizations typically see immediate productivity improvements within 30 days of deployment, with full ROI achieved in 6-12 months. The ROI calculation includes reduced search time, improved decision-making speed, and decreased compliance risks. Average annual savings range from $150,000 to $2.5 million depending on organization size and document complexity.
              </p>
            </div>
            
            <div class="glass-morphism p-6 rounded-xl">
              <h3 class="font-bold text-white mb-3">How do intelligent systems maintain accuracy as document repositories grow?</h3>
              <p class="text-gray-200 leading-relaxed">
                Intelligent systems use advanced indexing strategies, hierarchical storage, and continuous model updates to maintain performance at scale. Vector databases are optimized for similarity search across millions of documents, while machine learning models are retrained periodically on new content to maintain accuracy and relevance.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Call to Action -->
        <section class="glass-morphism p-8 rounded-xl text-center">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-orbitron font-bold text-primary mb-4">
            Upgrade to Intelligent Document Retrieval
          </h2>
          <p class="text-gray-200 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
            Don't let outdated search technology limit your organization's potential. 
            Discover how intelligent document retrieval can transform your knowledge access and decision-making processes.
          </p>
          <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4 justify-center">
            <button class="bg-primary text-black py-3 px-8 rounded-lg font-orbitron font-bold hover:bg-primary/80 transition-all duration-300">
              Get Implementation Consultation
            </button>
            <button class="border border-primary/30 text-primary py-3 px-8 rounded-lg font-orbitron font-bold hover:bg-primary/80 transition-all duration-300">
              Download Feature Checklist
            </button>
          </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Related Articles -->
        <section class="mt-16">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-orbitron font-bold text-white mb-6">Related Articles</h2>
          <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
            <a href="/blog/ai-document-management-system" class="glass-morphism p-6 rounded-xl hover:border-primary/50 transition-all duration-300 block">
              <h3 class="font-orbitron font-bold text-primary mb-2">AI Document Management System – Intelligent Retrieval & Organization for Business</h3>
              <p class="text-gray-300 text-sm">Complete guide to AI-powered document management solutions.</p>
            </a>
            <a href="/blog/ai-powered-document-classification" class="glass-morphism p-6 rounded-xl hover:border-primary/50 transition-all duration-300 block">
              <h3 class="font-orbitron font-bold text-primary mb-2">AI-Powered Document Classification: Automating Compliance & Organization</h3>
              <p class="text-gray-300 text-sm">Learn how AI automates document classification and compliance monitoring.</p>
            </a>
          </div>
        </section>

      </div>
    </article>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</Layout>